  "original_title": "\u0b86\u0b95\u0bb8\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bc8 \u0b87\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bbf \u0baa\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0b9a\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bc8 \u0b9a\u0bc6\u0baf\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bc1\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0ba9\u0bc6\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd ; \u0b95\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bbf \u0b85\u0bae\u0bc8\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "School activities will be conducted without August vacation; Ministry of Education",
      "author": "Digital Desk 5",
      "body_lines": [
        "All government and government-recognised private schools will continue their school activities without holidays in August. Also Grade 5 Scholarship Examination and G.E.T. According to the Ministry of Education, the high-level exams have been decided to be held in November.",
        "It has been decided to carry out continuous education activities in view of the standard 5 proficiency examination and G.E.D. higher examinations.",
        "Accordingly, all government and government recognized private schools will carry out continuous educational activities from tomorrow. Accordingly, the school activities will continue till the end of November without vacation in August.",
        "Various exams were postponed due to the economic crisis in the country. More exams are pending. It has been decided by the Ministry of Education to take this into consideration.",
        "Accordingly, the Grade 5 Scholarship Examination will be held on 27th November. Also, the G.E.C. High Level Examination is going to be held from November 28.",
        "In this case, G.B.E. High Level Examination is going to be conducted from 28th November to 23rd December.",
        "Also, educational activities will not be carried out in Grade 1 and 2 classes. The Ministry of Education is investigating the activities of carrying out various programs to identify the needs of students studying in Grade 3.",
        "155 officers who have obtained the basic equivalent marks of the Sri Lanka Presidential Service Limited Competitive Examination have been given fresh appointments related to grade 111 of the Sri Lanka Presidential Service.",
        "Also, K. P.D. The Ministry of Education has decided to start coaching courses through universities covering 24 core subjects for students appearing for higher level exams.",
        "Due to limited public transport due to fuel shortage, steps have been taken to engage private public transport buses for school students only.",
        "It is also mentioned in the report that school public transport buses will be in service from the day after tomorrow."
      ],
